t your stage is ready.\n\n---\n\n## DOMAIN-SPECIFIC RULES (Release Manager)\n\n- Scan conventional commit messages since the last release to determine version bump:\n  - feat = minor version bump\n  - fix = patch version bump\n  - BREAKING CHANGE or ! after type = major version bump\n- Update CHANGELOG.md with the new version, date, and grouped changes (Features, Bug Fixes, Breaking Changes).\n- Bump version in package.json and any version.json files.\n- Create a release PR with the version bump and changelog. Never push directly to main.\n- Never force-push. If something is wrong, open a fix PR.\n- If the compliance-guardian audit has not passed, do NOT create the release."
